    <id>tag:blue-mage.net,2009:/blog//1.8</id>

    <published>2009-10-29T16:27:21Z</published>
    <updated>2009-10-29T16:37:45Z</updated>

    <summary>Why am I terrible at blogging? I&apos;m a perfectionist at heart. And not just any old perfectionist but a categorical perfectionist. I want to write reviews of the books I&apos;m reading. And I&apos;ve read at least six since reading Federations,...</summary>
    <author>
        <name>Rob Hilton</name>
        
    </author>
    
        <category term="Random" scheme="http://www.sixapart.com/ns/types#category" />
    
    
    <content type="html" xml:lang="en" xml:base="http://blue-mage.net/blog/">
        <![CDATA[Why am I terrible at blogging? I'm a perfectionist at heart. And not just any old perfectionist but a categorical perfectionist. I want to write reviews of the books I'm reading. And I've read at least six since reading <i>Federations,</i> but I haven't managed to write about any of them because I want what I write to be so much better than that one.<br /><br />You know how your parents told you "if you're going to do something, do it well"? This is probably symptomatic of taking that old adage in reverse. If you can't do it well, don't bother doing it at all.<br /><br />But blogging <i>should</i> be the opposite of that. At least for those of us who aren't doing it professionally. It's a way to get my thoughts down and record for posterity of just how bad I really am at writing.<br /><br />And with all that said, I feel better now.<br /> ]]>
        
    </content>
</entry>

